text: William Betts may refer to: * William Betts (chaplain) (died 1535), supporter of Anne Boleyn * William Betts (umpire) (1865–1936), baseball umpire * William Betts (MP) (died 1738), Member of Parliament for Weymouth and Melcombe Regis, 1710, 1713 and 1715–1730 * William Vallance Betts (1862–1933), English architect * William Betts (1790–1867), English contractor's agent and railway contractor, father of Edward Betts * Billy Betts (1864–1941), English football player
